Sentencas: This paper presents a multiphysical modeling of a two-dimensional (2-D) reversible tubular solid oxide cell.
Titulo: Multidimensional Reversible Solid Oxide Fuel Cell Modeling for Embedded Applications

Sentencas: The developed model can represent both a solid oxide electrolysis cell (SOEC) and solid oxide fuel cell (SOFC) operations.
Titulo: Multidimensional Reversible Solid Oxide Fuel Cell Modeling for Embedded Applications

Sentencas: By taking into account of the electrochemical, fluidic, and thermal physical phenomena, the presented model can accurately describe the multiphysical effects inside a cell for both fuel cell and electrolysis cell operation under entire working range of cell current and temperature.
Titulo: Multidimensional Reversible Solid Oxide Fuel Cell Modeling for Embedded Applications

Sentencas: In addition, an iterative solver is proposed which is used to solve the 2-D distribution of physical quantities along the tubular cell.
Titulo: Multidimensional Reversible Solid Oxide Fuel Cell Modeling for Embedded Applications

Sentencas: The proposed model is suitable for embedded applications, such as real-time simulation or online diagnostic control.
Titulo: Multidimensional Reversible Solid Oxide Fuel Cell Modeling for Embedded Applications

Sentencas: The reversible solid oxide cell model is then validated experimentally in both SOEC and SOFC configurations under different species partial pressures, operating temperatures, and current densities conditions.
Titulo: Multidimensional Reversible Solid Oxide Fuel Cell Modeling for Embedded Applications
